HEADWORD: Damnably
<hw>Dam"na*bly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a manner to
incur severe censure, condemnation, or punishment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Odiously; detestably; excessively.</def>
<mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Damnation</ent>⟦br⟧
